  "title" : "Checking that a List is not empty in Hamcrest",
  "body" : "<p>I was wondering if anyone knew of a way to check if a List is empty using <code>assertThat()</code> and <code>Matchers</code>?</p>\n\n<p>Best way I could see just use JUnit:</p>\n\n<pre><code>assertFalse(list.isEmpty());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>But I was hoping that there was some way to do this in Hamcrest.</p>\n"
